<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_002-5a.136" xml:lang="en">Rewards</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_002-5a.137" xml:lang="en">are means by which one encourages the loyal and the capable,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_002-5a.139" xml:lang="en">but they are also that by which one brings about vulgar competition.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_002-5a.141" xml:lang="en">NOTE:</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_002-5a.142" xml:lang="en">The important point in governing a state</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_002-5a.198" xml:lang="en">is to use (for this purpose) humaneness and rectitude (i.e. morality), reward and punishment.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_002-5a.905" xml:lang="en">This is the general rule.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_002-5a.907" xml:lang="en">And yet, when one does not do this in a way that fits the situation,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_002-5a.916" xml:lang="en">one does create harm.</seg>
</p>
</div>
