<div><head>反經第十三</head>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.4" xml:lang="en">I have heard/learnt that the annihilation of the Three Dynasties</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.5" xml:lang="en">was not a matter of the laws being annihilated,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.6" xml:lang="en">it was a matter of the the controllers of the law not being the right kind of people.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.7" xml:lang="en">Therefore, when it comes the proper understanding of law</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.8" xml:lang="en">and to what we know of the actions of the Former Kings,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.9" xml:lang="en">then, if they had not been the right sort of people</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.10" xml:lang="en">(their) Way would not all by itself have got implemented.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.11" xml:lang="en">Therefore the Yīnwénzǐ says:</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.15" xml:lang="en">constitiute the art of ruling the world of the Five Emperors and the Three Kings.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.16" xml:lang="en">Now then: as for kind-heartedness</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.17" xml:lang="en">it that according to which one is broadly generous to other creatures (compare 人"others")</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.18" xml:lang="en">But it is also that through which one generates partiality and egotism.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.31" xml:lang="en">As for rectitude,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.32" xml:lang="en">it is a means by which to realise proper demeanour,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.33" xml:lang="en">but it is also a means by which to realise demonstrative pretense.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.34" xml:lang="en">This is the inverse of rectitude.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.35" xml:lang="en">NOTE:</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.36" xml:lang="en">To cause the ruin of one's person and sacrifice it for the state,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.37" xml:lang="en">when approaching an important juncture †not to be made to let go†,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.38" xml:lang="en">that is the right kind of rectitude.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.39" xml:lang="en">As in the case of Yú Qīng, the prime minister of Zhào,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.40" xml:lang="en">he gave up his prime-ministership and gave up his ruler</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.41" xml:lang="en">in order to completely avert the danger from [his friend] Wèi Qí.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.42" xml:lang="en">Or as in the case of Wú Jì of Xìnlíng,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.43" xml:lang="en">he stole a tally and forged an order</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.44" xml:lang="en">in order to come to the aid of [the Lord of] Píngyuán who was in trouble.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.45" xml:lang="en">The rectitude of turning one’s back on the public and dying for one's party was realised</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.46" xml:lang="en">but the proper behaviour of taking care of one's official duties and serving one's superiors was abandoned.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.47" xml:lang="en">That is why Máogōng berated Wú Jì:</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.48" xml:lang="en">For Zhào he produced positive results,</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.49" xml:lang="en">but for Wèi he was not a success.</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.50" xml:lang="en">All cases of this sort</seg>
<seg corresp="#KR3j0015_CH7x2006_004-1a.51" xml:lang="en">are cases of moral demonstrative pretense.)</seg>
</p>
